{
  "texts": [
    "For this reason the risk σ is called the ex-ante risk, to distinguish it from the standard deviation of the realized portfolio returns when trading, the ex-post risk.",
    "Similarly we refer to σ a as the ex-ante active risk.",
    "Optimizing expected return and risk.",
    "We have two objectives, high expected return and low risk.",
    "Perhaps the most common method for combining these objectives is to form a risk-adjusted return, R -γσ 2, where γ > 0 is the risk aversion parameter."
  ]
}